392 KB! That‚Äôs an amazing improvement from 7.6MB! üéâüéâüéâ</p>

<p>Conclusion
Writing Go code for the browser is a reality today. But it‚Äôs no picnic. Ideally, we‚Äôd write whatever we want, run the Go compiler and get a 1kb npm package or something, right? Well, we‚Äôll get there. Still a better love story than writing JavaScript, aye.</p>

